  RFC9765 [label="RFC9765
RADIUS/1.1: Leveraging Application-Layer
Protocol Negotiation (ALPN) to Remove
MD5
2025", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC9765.html", target="_top", tooltip="This document defines Application-Layer Protocol Negotiation (ALPN) extensions for use with RADIUS/TLS and RADIUS/DTLS. These extensions permit the negotiation of an application protocol variant of RADIUS called RADIUS/1.1. No changes are made to RADIUS/UDP or RADIUS/TCP. The extensions allow the negotiation of a transport profile where the RADIUS shared secret is no longer used, and all MD5-based packet authentication and attribute obfuscation methods are removed. This document updates RFCs 2865, 2866, 5176, 6613, 6614, and 7360."];
  RFC9765 -> updated_by;

